{"lemma":"رَقِيقٌ","slug":"رَقِيقٌ","root":"ر.ق.ق","root_slug":"ر-ق-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ق-ق","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16280"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%82%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"thin, fine, subtle"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"soft, sensitive, sentimental"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"slim"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"in narrow circumstances"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb رَقَّ (raqqa, “to become thin”). Compare Hebrew רַךְ (rakh, “soft”)."},"ipa":["/ra.qiːq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16280","headword_ar":"رَقِيقٌ","root":"rq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having the quality termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diq~apN","text_ar":"دِقَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA; [see 1, first sentence, respecting a mistranscription in the CK;]) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruqaAqN","text_ar":"رُقَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) of which the fem. is likewise with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruq~aAqN","text_ar":"رُقَّاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rum~aAnN","text_ar":"رُمَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiyZN","text_ar":"غَلِيظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raq~N","text_ar":"رَقٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riq~N","text_ar":"رِقٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaxiynN","text_ar":"ثَخِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) [or rather this last is the proper explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiyqN","text_ar":"رَقِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as well as of all the other epithets above mentioned; (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riq~apN","text_ar":"رِقَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thin"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having little thickness in comparison with its breadth and length together; having little extent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depth, between its two opposite surfaces:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] applied to bread that is [flat, flattened, or] expanded; such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruqaAqN","text_ar":"رُقَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.: (TA:) and to a garment, or piece of cloth, (Mgh, El-Munáwee, TA,) and the like, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thin, fine, delicate, flimsy, unsubstantial,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uncompact, in texture &c.; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SafiyqN","text_ar":"صَفِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (El-Munáwee, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruqaAriqN","text_ar":"رُقَارِقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and to water [as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shallow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of little depth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner to sand]: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruq~N","text_ar":"رُقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IDrd, K, TA:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thin"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wanting in spissitude;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to mud &c.:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attenuated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqaAqN","text_ar":"رِقَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ariq~apN","text_ar":"اَرِقَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aqiyqaAni","text_ar":"الرَّقِيقَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The part between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaASirap","text_ar":"خَاصِرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flank"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rufog","text_ar":"رُفْغ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"groin, on either side"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (AA, K:) and the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^arq~apu","text_ar":"الاَرقَّةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thin parts at the flanks of she-camels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK.) Also, the dual,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlrqyqAn","text_ar":"الرقيقان"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiDonaAni","text_ar":"حِضْنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part between the armpit and the flank, on either side"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, TA. [In the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxuSoyAni","text_ar":"الخُصْيانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]) And ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two veins called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axodaEaAni","text_ar":"اَخْدَعَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (K.) And, of the nose,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two sides:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) so says As: or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiyq","text_ar":"رَقِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the nose is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thin and soft part of the side."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attenuated, and consequently"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weak, in the bones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqaqN","text_ar":"رَقَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN raqiyqapN","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ رَقِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-camel whose marrow-bones have become weak and thin"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEufato waraq~ato","text_ar":"ضَعُفَتْ وَرَقَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and whose medullary canal is wide:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqaAqN","text_ar":"رِقَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqaAy^iqu","text_ar":"رَقَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, TA.) ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weak:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abject, mean, paltry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contemptible:"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a man [&c.]. (TA.) And goats are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlN raqiyqN","text_ar":"مَالٌ رَقِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weak cattle"},{"kind":"text","text":"] because they have not the endurance of sheep. (TA.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weak-hearted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiyqu Alqalobi","text_ar":"رَقِيقُ القَلْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender, of heart; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAsiY Alqalobi","text_ar":"قَاسِى القَلْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (El-Munáwee, TA.) ―         -b5-  [(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Soft"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy and sweet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elegant, graceful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ornate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"speech or language.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiyqu All~afoZi","text_ar":"رَقِيقُ اللَّفْظِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means [(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Soft"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of expression;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a man: and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy and sweet expression."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 8.) ―         -b6-  [(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Slender,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gentle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to the voice.] ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN raqiyqu AlHawaA$iY","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ رَقِيقُ الحَوَاشِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man gentle, gracious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"courteous, to his associates."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H$Y","text_ar":"حشى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayo$N raqiyqu AlHawaA$iY","text_ar":"عَيْشٌ رَقِيقُ الحَوَاشِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A soft"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"delicate, pleasant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plentiful and easy, life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b8-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayo$N raqiyqN","text_ar":"عَيْشٌ رَقِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may sometimes mean the same: but it commonly means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Scanty living"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sustenance."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b9-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN raqiyqu Ald~iyni","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ رَقِيقُ الدِّينِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlHaAli","text_ar":"وَالحَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is weak in respect of religion, and narrow in the circumstances of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil in, his state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riq~apN","text_ar":"رِقَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A slave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) [but] the latter is [also] called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiyqapN","text_ar":"رَقِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lh, JK, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slaves;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it is used as sing. and pl.; (S, Mgh, Msb, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafiyqN","text_ar":"رَفِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliyTN","text_ar":"خَلِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) accord. to Abu-l-'Abbás, so called because they are abject and submissive to their owner: (TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiyqN","text_ar":"رَقِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ariq~aA='u","text_ar":"اَرِقَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) erroneously said in the K to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqaAqN","text_ar":"رِقَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiyqapN","text_ar":"رَقِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqaAy^iqu","text_ar":"رَقَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lh, TA.) Using it as pl., you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`w^ulaA='i raqiyqiY","text_ar":"هٰوُلَا=ءِ رَقِيقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These are my slaves"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa fiY Alr~aqiyqi SadaqapN","text_ar":"لَيْسَ فِى الرَّقِيقِ صَدَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no poorrate"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the case of slaves used for service"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as distinguished from those that are for sale]. (Msb.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muraq~N","text_ar":"مُرَقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","IDrd","AA","Lh","JK"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}